    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-08-28T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-08-28T09:00:00-05:00" n="658"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d658">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">192/1675: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_SLA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-08-28T17:00:00+03:00"
                            >August 28, 1939—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 28—11:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>481. Embassy’s 474, August 26, 1 p.m. Inasmuch as the Foreign Office now declines
                    to accord the Embassy the courtesy of permitting <pb facs="0952" n="846"
                        xml:id="pg_846"/> Dr. <persName corresp="#p_NWG1">Nelson</persName> to have
                    his household effects and particularly his medical instruments and supplies
                    examined for export purposes by a customs officer at his place of residence and
                    insists that the examination take place in the Moscow customhouse which I regard
                    as unsanitary for the exposure of his already sterilized instruments and
                    supplies, I request that the courtesy of waiving a bill of health for the <hi
                        rend="italic">Kim</hi> be not granted unless and until a further telegram on
                    this subject is received from me. The courtesy being denied Dr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_NWG1">Nelson</persName> has been accorded heretofore to all
                    departing diplomatic officers of this Mission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SLA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
